Prima facie evidence suggests he is a man of impaired credibility for having been found by Parliament — no less — as not fit to lead! In this case, any organisation that deals with him or other leaders with integrity issues (particularly government institutions), need to apply common sense.
It should not be the work of the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission (EACC) alone but individual Kenyans, the Registrar of Political Parties included, and all other entities to disbar such individuals.



